<paragraph id="2AD7701090F558FA12A6416F103BAD56" pageId="0" pageNumber="119">
Professor Jian Huang (FAFU) confirmed our identification. Our specimens agree well with the original description in 
<bibRefCitation id="CE0BDD0D9893BE90F1CA5D654C04B1EE" author="Huang, J" journalOrPublisher="Chongqing Publishing House, Chongqing" pageId="0" pageNumber="119" refId="B21" refString="Huang, J, 1994. Systematic studies on Aphelinidae of China (Hymenoptera: Chalcidoidea). Chongqing Publishing House, Chongqing" title="Systematic studies on Aphelinidae of China (Hymenoptera: Chalcidoidea)." year="1994">Huang (1994)</bibRefCitation>
. A minor difference should be noted: mesoscutellum (Figs 
<figureCitation id="28EB1AB3374060DE058089CE5E221387" captionStart="Figures 1–8" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 8. Coccophagus anchoroides 1 body, dorsal view 2 head 3 antenna, inset shows the colour of outer surface of scape 4 mesosoma 5 fore wing 6 hind wing 7 mid leg 8 metasoma." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1091.80065.figures1-8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/666979" pageId="0" pageNumber="119">1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="BC0911AD22ED685A97B75C32047EE046" captionStart="Figures 1–8" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 8. Coccophagus anchoroides 1 body, dorsal view 2 head 3 antenna, inset shows the colour of outer surface of scape 4 mesosoma 5 fore wing 6 hind wing 7 mid leg 8 metasoma." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1091.80065.figures1-8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/666979" pageId="0" pageNumber="119">4</figureCitation>
) of our specimens with two yellow curved stripes anteriorly like 
<taxonomicName id="5E8D4A7866623F9FE3DAB37BF75810B0" class="Insecta" genus="C." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="C. yunnana" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yunnana">
<emphasis id="B93DEABD5EC6AA81BA0CBFCCC9F5EF38" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="119">C. yunnana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but in the original description mesoscutellum without yellow markings anteriorly (cf. fig. 90C in 
<bibRefCitation id="B80D5055D6F4AA3B335D2DB6706264A9" author="Huang, J" journalOrPublisher="Chongqing Publishing House, Chongqing" pageId="0" pageNumber="119" refId="B21" refString="Huang, J, 1994. Systematic studies on Aphelinidae of China (Hymenoptera: Chalcidoidea). Chongqing Publishing House, Chongqing" title="Systematic studies on Aphelinidae of China (Hymenoptera: Chalcidoidea)." year="1994">Huang 1994</bibRefCitation>
). Here we provided the digital images and DNA sequence for references.
</paragraph>
